---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = '9 June 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Legal Terms"
  description="Terms of use, disclaimer and editorial policy for The Attaché Desk."
>
  <section class="page-head">
    <div class="shell page-head__inner">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><span>Legal Terms</span>
      </nav>
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--on-navy">Reference</span>
      <h1>Legal Terms</h1>
      <p class="page-head__lede">Terms of use, disclaimer and editorial policy.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <article class="prose">
        <div class="note">
          <strong>Template — review required</strong>
          This page is a plain-language starting point, not finished legal text.
          Replace the bracketed placeholders and have it reviewed by qualified
          counsel in the relevant jurisdiction before publishing. Items marked
          [&hellip;] need real operator details.
        </div>

        <p class="ref" style="margin-top:1.6rem;">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <h2>1. Who runs this site</h2>
        <p>
          The Attaché Desk (&ldquo;the Site&rdquo;) is operated by [Operator legal
          name], [registered address], reachable at [contact email]. References to
          &ldquo;we&rdquo; and &ldquo;us&rdquo; mean the operator.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Nature of the content</h2>
        <p>
          The Site is an editorial reference. Its content is general information
          for diplomats, consular staff and international officials. It is
          <strong>not</strong> legal, tax, immigration, financial, security or
          relocation advice, and no professional relationship is created by using
          it. Rules and procedures vary by mission, accreditation, nationality and
          personal circumstances, and they change over time.
        </p>

        <h2>3. No reliance; verify before acting</h2>
        <p>
          Do not rely on the Site as the basis for any decision affecting your
          status, entitlements or obligations. Always confirm specifics with your
          mission, the host-country authorities and the relevant official sources
          before acting. To the extent permitted by law, we accept no liability
          for loss arising from reliance on the content.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Accuracy and corrections</h2>
        <p>
          We aim to keep guides current and to date-stamp them, but we do not
          warrant that the content is complete, accurate or up to date. If you
          spot an error, write to [corrections email] and we will review it.
        </p>

        <h2>5. External links</h2>
        <p>
          The Site links to third-party sources, including official authorities.
          We are not responsible for the content, accuracy or availability of
          external sites, and a link is not an endorsement.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          Unless stated otherwise, the editorial content, layout and branding of
          the Site are owned by the operator or its licensors. You may read and
          share links to the content for personal, non-commercial use.
          Republication or systematic copying requires written permission.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          [Describe what data, if any, the Site collects — for example analytics
          or none — and link to a separate Privacy Policy if required by
          applicable law, such as the GDPR.]
        </p>

        <h2>8. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms from time to time. The &ldquo;last
          updated&rdquo; date above reflects the current version.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of [jurisdiction], and disputes are
          subject to the courts of [jurisdiction], without prejudice to any
          mandatory consumer protections that apply to you.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
